outcomes.title: Statistical Graphs
outcomes.template:
A critical component to our understanding of statistics is being able to read and understand graphs. It is also critical that we be able to look at graphs and identify any flaws they might have. Be sure to answer ALL the questions.

Ivy League Admissions, Class of 2020

Use the graph above to answer the questions.

What type of graph is this?

bar graph

What percent of all applicants to {{var_name1}} are accepted? What information in the graph tells you this answer?

{{percentage_value1}}%

What do the {{color}} bars on the graph mean in the context of the real world?

{{color_meaning}}

According to the graph, how many applicants {{action}} {{var_name2}} for the class of 2020?

{{var_big2}}

outcomes.template:
A critical component to our understanding of statistics is being able to read and understand graphs. It is also critical that we be able to look at graphs and identify any flaws they might have. Be sure to answer ALL the questions.

Essential Workers

Use the graph above to answer the questions.

What type of graph is this?

A bar graph.

What percent of {{job_2}} workers were women? What information in the graph tells you this answer?

{{answer_2}}%. The number inside the bars.

What does the {{total_3}} in the line that says "{{job_3}}" mean in the context of the information presented by the graph?

That means there were a total of {{total_3}} people working as {{job_3}} workers

According to the graph, approximately how many women worked as {{job_4}}?

.{{answer_4p}} x {{answer_4t}} = {{answer_4}}

Some people have argued that women are impacted more than men by requiring essential workers to continue working during the pandemic. Do you agree or disagree with this statement? Why? Use information provided by the graph to support your argument.

Answers will vary.

Use the graph above to answer the questions.

line graph or a time series graph

The x-axis is time and the y-axis is percent of people wearing mask in public.

The percentage of people wearing face coverings in public in {{answer_3}} from February to July

Compare {{country_4a}} and {{country_4b}} in {{month_4}}. What is happening?

{{answer_4}}

The data wasn't available; wasn't collected; or wasn't shared.

The overall percentage is going up. (other details can be given)

A critical component to our understanding of statistics is being able to read and understand graphs. It is also critical that we be able to look at graphs and identify any flaws they might have. Be sure to answer ALL the questions.

Percentage of smokers by household income

Use the graph above to answer the questions.

What type of graph is this?

bar graph

Could you use a {{graph_2}} graph to display this data? Why or why not?

No, {{answer_2}}

What percent of people whose household income is {{money_3}} smoke "every day" or "some days"? What information in the graph tells you this answer?

{{answer_3}}%, the number inside the bar.

What does the number in the bar in the {{money_4}} line mean in the context of the information presented by the graph?

Out of the households that make {{money_4}}, {{answer_4}}% of them has someone that smokes some or every day in them.

What is the trend in the percent of people who smoke "every day" or "some days" as household income {{dir_5}}? Justify your answer with evidence from the graph.

As the household income level {{dir_5}}, the percentage of smoker in the income level {{answer_5}}

outcomes.template:
A critical component to our understanding of statistics is being able to read and understand graphs. It is also critical that we be able to look at graphs and identify any flaws they might have. Be sure to answer ALL the questions.

Share of ransomware attacks by industry type.

Use the graph above to answer the questions.

What type of graph is this?

bar graph

Could you use a {{graph_2}} graph to display this data? Why or why not?

{{answer_2}}

What does the number at the end of the bar in the {{industry_3}} line mean in the context of the information presented by the graph?

{{answer_3}}% of ransomware attacks from July 2020 to June 2021, were made against companies in the {{industry_3}} industry.

If we assume that the total number of ransomware attacks that occured between July 2020 and June 2021 was {{attack_4}}, how many attacks were there against companies in the {{industry_4}} sector?

{{answer_4}}

outcomes.title: Statistical Graphs
outcomes.template:
A critical component to our understanding of statistics is being able to read and understand graphs. It is also critical that we be able to look at graphs and identify any flaws they might have. Be sure to answer ALL the questions.

Scenario:

The U.S. job market was stronger than expected in June 2022, with payrolls growing by 372,000 additional jobs. The chart below summarizes the increase (or decrease) in total jobs in a variety of sectors.

The increase (or decrease) in total jobs in a variety of sectors.

Use the graph above to answer the questions.

What type of graph is this?

bar graph

Could you use a {{graph_2}} graph to display this data? Why or why not?

{{answer_2}}

What does the number at the end of the bar in the {{industry_3}} line mean in the context of the information presented by the graph?

The {{industry_3}} sector had an increase of {{answer_3}} jobs in June 2022.

Based on the information given above the graph, what percentage of the jobs added were in the {{industry_4}} sector? Be sure to show all work including anything plugged into a calculator. Round your percentage to 2 decimal places.

{{answer_4n}} / 372,000 = {{answer_4}}%

In 2021, Asian American workers face the longest periods of joblessness and other labor challenges, despite having the lowest unemployment rate out of any racial or ethnic group in the U.S. The chart below summarizes the median duration of joblessness for different racial groups, as well as the subgroups of race split by gender.

Use the graph above to answer the questions.

bar graph or multi-bar graph

It is the median joblessness in weeks for {{race_2}} {{answer_2}} in 2021.
